1
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,640
Dao!

2
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,080
PREVIOUSLY

3
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:27,680
Petch!

4
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,640
How dare you?

5
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,600
Stop!

6
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,680
<i>The police should be arresting</i>
<i>Petch by now.</i>

7
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:37,520
You're evil! How could you do that?

8
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:40,160
Everything that happened
was because of music!

9
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,200
You sneaked out to see the concert!

10
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:43,880
I was just trying to protect a girl.

11
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,640
This is my last warning to you!

12
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,240
Don't let this happen again!

13
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,600
Do whatever it takes

14
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,760
<i>to kick Petch</i>

15
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,080
<i>out of school.</i>

16
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,480
The school can no longer keep you.

17
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,680
So you must keep this between us.

18
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,200
Do you know a man named Petch?

19
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,720
Are you looking for Petch?

20
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,040
I'm sorry.

21
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,399
I didn't mean to.

22
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:19,920
Dao!

23
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,680
It's dangerous.

24
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,680
I didn't know that.

25
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,400
All I know is you've changed.

26
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,960
Where is the Petch that I know?

27
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,800
I am what I am.

28
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:36,360
I'm not as nice as you think.

29
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:39,320
I didn't expect you
to be a nice guy or anything.

30
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,720
I just want you to be reasonable.

31
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:45,800
About what?

32
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,760
When you wanted to text me,

33
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,760
you did.

34
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:59,040
When you didn't want to,
you just ghosted me.

35
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,680
Do you have any idea how I would feel?

36
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,840
Did you block me?

37
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:12,360
No.

38
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,520
I got bored with social media.

39
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,400
Petch, wait.

40
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,480
Did I do anything wrong?

41
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:28,160
It's me, not you.
I was wrong because I was born poor.

42
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,400
I got expelled.

43
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:34,560
I have to work at the garage
to help Dad pay his debt.

44
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,920
I have nothing else to talk to you about.

45
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
That doesn't make sense at all.

46
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,960
It does.

47
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,680
We're too different.

48
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,440
You come from a wealthy family.

49
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,600
And look at me.

50
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,240
I am a garage worker.

51
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,720
We have nothing in common.

52
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:03,160
Please get back to your beautiful world.

53
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:06,360
I'll be in my poor and pathetic world.

54
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,720
We shouldn't see each other again.

55
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,240
Leave.

56
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:22,920
I get it.

57
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,640
Good luck.

58
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,280
Dao!

59
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:50,920
Dao!

60
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,200
Dao.

61
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,280
You shouted at her
when she was in front of you.

62
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,200
You're shouting her name when she's gone.

63
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,320
Dam.

64
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,080
Answer me.

65
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,840
Are you out of your mind?

66
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,480
Keep it. You know nothing.

67
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,280
Right. I know nothing.

68
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:12,640
But I know that Natedao
came to see you at school.

69
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:15,640
She also knew that you got expelled.

70
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,920
But she asked me to take her here.

71
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,560
Remember this.

72
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:26,680
Only a lunatic like you
would reject Ms. Natedao.

73
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,680
She is too good for me.

74
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:35,360
I don't want to pull her down to my level.

75
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:40,920
You idiot.

76
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,560
Okay.

77
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,000
If so,

78
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,280
I would say one thing.

79
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,640
You can erase
anything you want from your mind.

80
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:59,840
But are you sure
that you can erase Dao from your memory?

81
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,760
There you are.

82
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,640
I was about to look for you at school.

83
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,640
I told you she would be here.

84
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,799
Dao…

85
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,840
Are you hungry?
Do you want to order something?

86
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:41,520
No. I want to go home.

87
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:41,040
How is Dao doing?

88
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,760
Don't you worry.

89
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,800
I won't let her out of my sight.

90
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,240
- All right.
- What about you?

91
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,560
Did you find something suspicious?

92
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,480
Not at all.

93
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,520
I always check her social media,
but there isn't anything to worry about.

94
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,600
Petch has probably
come to his senses by now

95
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,880
because Dao is way out of his league.

96
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,560
I hope so.

97
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:10,960
A lowlife like him
can't afford to take care of Dao.

98
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:15,000
Excuse me.

99
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:18,800
The master invites both of you
to join him for breakfast.

100
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,520
Thanks. I'll be there.

101
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,800
Yes, ma'am.

102
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,280
Please be my eyes and ears.

103
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:31,760
Sure.

104
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,840
Honestly,

105
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,880
apart from you,

106
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:40,280
I don't see anyone who could be
an anchor for Dao's life.

107
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,440
And the one I expect to be my son-in-law

108
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,240
is you.

109
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,600
Dao.

110
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,240
Are you on a diet?
You barely ate anything.

111
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,760
Is that so?

112
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:11,160
You're tiny. Are you really on a diet?

113
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,880
No, I'm not on a diet.

114
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,880
I just lost my appetite.

115
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,520
I'll wait in the car.

116
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,760
See you later, Dad, Mom.

117
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,520
Wait, sweetie.

118
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,880
I have something for you.

119
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,800
What is it?

120
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:42,840
Here.

121
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:45,520
I submitted a piano contest
application for you.

122
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,320
REGULATIONS FOR ALL
PIANO COMPETITION CATEGORIES

123
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:49,800
Why didn't you tell me about it?

124
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:52,360
I'm not sure whether I can make it.

125
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,720
Oh, dear.

126
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,520
What do you have to be afraid of?

127
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:59,720
You're both talented and well-disciplined.

128
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,760
You'll win first place for sure.

129
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,160
But I don't want to participate.

130
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:09,080
No. You have to.

131
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:12,680
Besides, Madam Rangsima,
the president of this contest,

132
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:16,680
is discussing land development
with your father and me.

133
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:19,400
You have to participate. Understand?

134
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:22,000
Yes.

135
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,040
Good girl.

136
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:38,040
I can't say no anyway.

137
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:51,920
Drunk?

138
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,640
I'm not drunk.

139
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,480
Where are you guys?

140
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,560
Right. Okay. See you there.

141
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,080
Hey.

142
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,760
That is for my friend.

143
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:45,320
Thank you for fixing
the water pump for me.

144
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,360
My pleasure, Venerable Grandfather.

145
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,960
I'm always at your service.

146
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:51,840
Goodbye.

147
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:53,280
Be well and happy.

148
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:58,600
You're about to leave,
but Dam hasn't shown up yet.

149
00:14:59,640 --> 00:15:02,240
I can hear you, Venerable Grandfather.

150
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:06,080
Still have the nerve
to talk back to me, Dam?

151
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,240
Where have you been then?

152
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,440
That's what I’m saying.

153
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:14,320
I called him many times,
but he turned off his phone.

154
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,680
My battery died.

155
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:20,560
If it didn't, you would have seen
a stray dog get beaten up.

156
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,200
Did you have a fight?

157
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,200
I've been living with
Venerable Grandfather since childhood.

158
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,640
I've never started a fight.

159
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:36,920
Am I right, Venerable Grandfather?

160
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,920
If they started a fight,

161
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,880
you shouldn't have
responded to them with violence.

162
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,680
<i>Sathu.</i>

163
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:50,840
"Vengeance is never ceased by vengeance."

164
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:53,480
But if they hold a grudge
like a dog with a bone,

165
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:56,600
they deserve to learn a lesson.

166
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:58,120
Otherwise,

167
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,120
there will be no good-hearted people
left in this world.

168
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,040
Oh, really?

169
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:04,000
You still have the nerve
to talk back to me.

170
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,360
I didn't talk back to you.

171
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,880
I just want you to know

172
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,000
that I can accept any form of insult,

173
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:17,120
but I can't stand seeing
the person I worship getting hurt.

174
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,520
Like you, sir.

175
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:22,400
And Petch, my best friend.

176
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:26,040
Let me get my things. I'll send you off.

177
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:37,320
AIR-CONDITIONED BUS, 10 BAHT

178
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:51,040
<i>You are out of reach</i>

179
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:56,920
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

180
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:03,160
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

181
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:09,079
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

182
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:14,079
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

183
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:20,480
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

184
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:24,960
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

185
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,960
We're not going
to see each other again, are we?

186
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:32,640
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

187
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:13,360
Dao.

188
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:17,480
After your piano class,
I'll pick you up for dinner.

189
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,520
Wait, Dao.

190
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,920
Could you please play me one love song?

191
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,880
Let go. I'll join my class now.

192
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,600
Keep on playing hard to get.

193
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,040
One day, you'll know.

194
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,640
Petch.

195
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,560
Petch.

196
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:02,480
Hey.

197
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:06,360
I bought <i>kaprao kai</i>
and cooked sunny-side up for you.

198
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:08,120
Put it there.

199
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,720
Let me finish my work here.

200
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:11,960
Hardworking man.

201
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,040
Ma'am.

202
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:32,560
How may I help you?

203
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:35,160
I'm looking for Petch.

204
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:36,880
Oh, Petch.

205
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,880
He's inside. Keep straight and turn right.

206
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,760
- Thank you so much.
- All right.

207
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,840
And what about your new school?

208
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,920
Have you submitted the application?

209
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:57,960
I'll start next semester.

210
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,800
My dad is still recovering at home.

211
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,280
I'd like to make money to pay his debt.

212
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,400
How much more do you need?

213
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,360
Ten grand.

214
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,840
Ten grand?

215
00:20:13,560 --> 00:20:15,480
How many more months
do you have to work for that?

216
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:28,160
According to what Petch had posted,
it should be this house.

217
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,680
"House Number 239/16."

218
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,800
239/16.

219
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,320
Here it is.

220
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,520
239/16.

221
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:51,960
"Mr. Nop Panjin."

222
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,920
The same surname as Petch's.

223
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:05,920
Good afternoon, sir.

224
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,920
Who are you looking for, girl?

225
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:12,960
Are you

226
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:15,040
Nop Panjin?

227
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:16,760
Yes.

228
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:21,080
Congratulations!

229
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,960
You won 10,000 baht
as a prize from our company.

230
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:27,120
Prize?

231
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,000
Ten grand?

232
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:30,120
Yes.

233
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:47,440
Are you being serious, girl?

234
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,440
Did I really win ten grand?

235
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:52,760
Yes.

236
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:57,040
You won the lottery from the company.

237
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:59,200
I'm the representative
to hand you the prize.

238
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:02,640
But I've never sent my name
for any lottery.

239
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:05,400
Well…

240
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:06,920
Yes, you did.

241
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:10,880
Here it is.

242
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,000
The product from our company.

243
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,760
I think I really…

244
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:18,760
never sent it.

245
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:25,080
Maybe another family member
sent your name.

246
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:27,280
I see.

247
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:29,720
Maybe Petch sent it.

248
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,680
He is my son.

249
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:33,320
I bet he did.

250
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:38,280
My son never tells me a single thing.

251
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:41,120
My son…

252
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,640
You're probably his age.

253
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,400
Have you graduated?

254
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:49,040
No, I haven't.

255
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:52,280
I'm still in high school,

256
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,680
but I work part-time on weekends.

257
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,240
You're a hardworking girl.

258
00:22:58,040 --> 00:23:01,520
I wish my son
were half as hardworking as you.

259
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,240
He's already hardworking.

260
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:05,480
Do you know him?

261
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,080
Well…

262
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,960
No, I mean…

263
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:14,560
Your son must be
a hardworking and generous man.

264
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,520
Do you smell anything?

265
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,000
Shoot!

266
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:30,400
I was heating up my soup.
I probably burnt it.

267
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:31,800
Ouch.

268
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:34,200
- Sir?
- My wound hurts.

269
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:37,000
- Ouch.
- May I take a look at it?

270
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,240
Well…

271
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:52,080
The soup is all burnt.

272
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,520
It's not edible.

273
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:58,520
So what would you have for lunch?

274
00:23:58,600 --> 00:23:59,680
Well…

275
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,480
I'll have instant noodles. It's simple.

276
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:05,960
I think you should eat a nutritious meal.

277
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:07,960
The thing is…

278
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:12,120
I don't have anything to eat.
My fridge is empty.

279
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:17,520
If you don't mind,
I would like to take care of your meal.

280
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:27,680
Hey. This is excellent.

281
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,280
Your work is neat and fast.

282
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,400
I tried my best
to uphold the garage's reputation.

283
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,080
I'll give you a raise this month.

284
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:41,840
Thank you, sir!

285
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:45,480
Thank you so much for accepting him.

286
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:49,560
I guarantee he won't let you down.
His work will be worth every baht you pay.

287
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,120
I couldn't agree more.

288
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,320
Yes.

289
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,600
Where is the girl?

290
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:58,400
- Where is she now?
- The girl?

291
00:24:58,920 --> 00:24:59,960
The girl?

292
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:01,880
What girl?

293
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,320
She was looking for you.

294
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:06,400
There was no girl here.

295
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,560
Exactly. I didn't see her.

296
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:11,360
She was looking for Petch
and I told her that you were here.

297
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:13,800
It is okay. No biggie.

298
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:16,560
You two should go home. All work is done.

299
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:17,880
- All right.
- Thank you, sir.

300
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,760
Petch.

301
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,880
Who was looking for you?

302
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,160
How would I know?

303
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,840
I stuck with you the whole day.

304
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,080
But forget it.

305
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:34,000
- I'll get a raise.
- A raise!

306
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,320
Your meal is ready.

307
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,200
I ordered you a main dish and snacks.

308
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,880
You shouldn't have bothered.

309
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,840
It's okay. I'm willing to help.

310
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:49,400
I'll get them on a plate for you.

311
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,400
No need, girl. I'll do it myself.

312
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:55,720
Please join me for this meal.

313
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:58,400
I'm afraid I can't.

314
00:25:58,480 --> 00:26:01,680
After handing you the prize,
I have another appointment.

315
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:03,920
You're a generous young woman.

316
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,320
I have a lunchbox and a prize.

317
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:08,840
You know what?

318
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:10,600
This amount of money

319
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:13,280
is very important to my family.

320
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:14,840
What prize?

321
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,680
Petch. There he is.

322
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:25,200
She came to hand me the prize
for the lottery entry you sent in my name.

323
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,400
I never sent anything for the lottery.

324
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:30,600
I thought so.

325
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:33,200
There might be some misunderstanding.

326
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:36,560
Right. And very inappropriate.

327
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,320
Right.

328
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,880
I've gotten too involved.

329
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:48,560
But I really want to help you.

330
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:52,880
Dao.

331
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:53,960
Dao!

332
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,200
Wait, girl!

333
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:00,760
How much did she give you?

334
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:02,280
Ten grand.

335
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:03,960
Ten grand?

336
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:06,520
Exactly what you need.

337
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:09,280
Did she know?

338
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,680
So you two know each other?

339
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:19,760
Give me the money. I'll return it to her.

340
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:23,640
Petch.

341
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:25,800
Don't follow him.

342
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,720
Let them figure it out.

343
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:30,440
So you

344
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:32,160
know everything, don't you?

345
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,880
I don't know much.

346
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,160
All I know is that

347
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,880
both of them know each other.

348
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,400
Dao!

349
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,600
Dao! Wait!

350
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,160
Hey.

351
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:48,880
Keep it.

352
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,320
It's for Mr. Nop.

353
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:51,720
Not you.

354
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:55,600
Is this how rich people pity the poor?

355
00:27:59,080 --> 00:27:59,960
Petch.

356
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,560
Are you having fun?

357
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:06,760
Is it fun to be a philanthropist,
throwing money at the poor?

358
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:08,560
I didn't see it like that!

359
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,000
I just wanted to help you.

360
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:15,280
Is it so wrong
if a friend wants to help a friend?

361
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:18,440
You can't earn friendship with money.

362
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,400
Here.

363
00:28:22,360 --> 00:28:23,280
Keep it.

364
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:26,640
And I'm so sorry

365
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,440
that your money is not valuable here.

366
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,560
Of course, I have money!

367
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:48,160
But you're heartless!

368
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,560
We are equals.

369
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:58,400
Why do you have to treat me like this?

370
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:02,280
Was I so wrong for being born rich?

371
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,160
No.

372
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:05,840
You weren't wrong.

373
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:08,440
It was me.

374
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,560
I was wrong

375
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,360
for being born poor.

376
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,600
You're insane.

377
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:22,760
You stopped being friends with me
because of the barrier you've made up?

378
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:24,080
Yes!

379
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,680
That's what I'm talking about.

380
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:29,120
Now, we're on the same page.

381
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:32,560
Fine.

382
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:38,360
If my generosity hurts your ego,

383
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:41,360
then I'm sorry.

384
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:51,560
Even though I have no right
to be your friend…

385
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:55,400
let me say one thing.

386
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,480
I came here today

387
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:05,000
because I'll be at a piano contest

388
00:30:07,520 --> 00:30:10,240
and I want emotional support
from you the most.

389
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,480
Whether you come to support me,

390
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,480
it's your call.

391
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,400
Dao! Wait!

392
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:10,200
VACANT

393
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:14,240
Dao!

394
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,160
Dao! Wait!

395
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:18,160
Dao!

396
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,920
What have I done?

397
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,200
Petch?

398
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:04,280
I thought you had already left.

399
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:07,960
I would like to keep myself busy.

400
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:10,960
Feel free to order me any work.

401
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:13,800
I like that you're being hardworking.

402
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,680
I have one side job. Are you in?

403
00:32:16,520 --> 00:32:17,440
What is it?

404
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:19,320
Modify the car engine.

405
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:21,720
I'll give you 15,000. Are you in?

406
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,000
Fifteen grand?

407
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:28,920
- I'm in. Thank you.
- Good.

408
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:31,520
I like a hardworking man.

409
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:32,640
I really like it.

410
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:42,720
<i>"Satima Sukha Su…"</i>

411
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,560
<i>"Sukha…"</i>

412
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,360
<i>"Su… Su…"</i>

413
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:49,400
Can you read it?

414
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:51,920
Well…

415
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:56,560
It is quite dark in here,
so I barely see it.

416
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:57,800
Liar!

417
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,240
Venerable Grandfather!

418
00:33:00,320 --> 00:33:03,400
If you hit me, I won't join you
for the morning activity.

419
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:04,720
- Ouch!
- Right.

420
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:05,960
You're faking it.

421
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:09,760
But you're fearless

422
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:11,960
when it comes to fighting.

423
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:16,000
Well, a man should have his ego.

424
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:19,400
When anger comes, he must fight.

425
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:22,280
I'll help you read it.

426
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:30,680
<i>"Satima Sukhavihari."</i>

427
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:34,120
"The mindful one
will live an unwavering peaceful life."

428
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,960
Oh, I see.

429
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:41,680
Listen to me, boy.

430
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,840
There is goodness in you.

431
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:48,320
But you can be impulsive.

432
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:51,440
If you fail to manage your emotions,

433
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:54,720
if you let emotions control you,

434
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:56,920
disaster will come.

435
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:00,120
<i>Sathu.</i>

436
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:03,440
Unexpected food for thought.

437
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,480
Don't joke about it.

438
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:13,920
Your parents sent you here
because they wanted you to be good.

439
00:34:15,719 --> 00:34:17,480
Whenever you lose your way,

440
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:21,280
let the memory
of your departed parents ground you.

441
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:24,840
Understood.

442
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,360
I won't be impulsive.

443
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:30,239
And I'll be more mindful.

444
00:34:37,639 --> 00:34:39,320
<i>Namasakarn</i>, Venerable Grandfather.

445
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:44,679
You're late.
You must be busy at the garage.

446
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,800
The work just kept coming.

447
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,320
And what brings you here?

448
00:34:51,080 --> 00:34:53,040
I just want to talk to Dam.

449
00:34:58,400 --> 00:34:59,240
Here.

450
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:00,720
What is it?

451
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:02,320
Return it for me.

452
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:10,240
"The invitation to be the audience
of the Piano Competition…"

453
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:11,640
Return to whom?

454
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:12,960
To Natedao.

455
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:14,280
What?

456
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:18,360
She came today to give me this invitation.

457
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:20,200
But I've considered…

458
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:22,640
I shouldn't go.

459
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,880
That would be rude of you.

460
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:27,200
Ms. Natedao invited you.

461
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,480
She wanted you to see her perform.

462
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,880
Why return it?

463
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,200
No more questions.

464
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:33,880
Just do as I said.

465
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:35,680
Petch.

466
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:37,960
You're being too arrogant right now.

467
00:35:38,760 --> 00:35:41,720
Natedao was so nice to you,
but you pushed her away.

468
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:43,080
Are you insane?

469
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:44,160
I'm insane.

470
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:46,080
Dao is too good for me.

471
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:49,080
She doesn't need to lower herself for me.

472
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:51,720
Petch, can you think it through again?

473
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:52,920
Not a word.

474
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:55,680
How much money did she give you?

475
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,440
Five grand.

476
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,320
Five grand.

477
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:08,160
Return this to her too.

478
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,520
You're being too much.

479
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,560
I know.

480
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,280
If you're a real friend of mine,

481
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:19,480
I hope you can do me this favor.

482
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:39,600
Duean.

483
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,800
I met a girl named Dao.

484
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:45,680
She is a generous girl.

485
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:49,760
She has many things in common with you.

486
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:56,920
Petch.

487
00:36:58,040 --> 00:36:59,360
Why are you still awake, Dad?

488
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:01,800
I was waiting for you.

489
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:05,160
I want to know about Dao.

490
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,440
There's nothing.

491
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:11,160
We're just acquaintances.

492
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,160
Don't lie to me.

493
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:14,800
If you're not close to her,

494
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,800
she wouldn't have the nerve to come here.

495
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:20,520
There is nothing between us.

496
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:23,280
And she won't come here again.

497
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:28,120
Wait.

498
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:31,320
What's wrong?
What is going on with you two?

499
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,440
Did you cause trouble again?

500
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:35,920
She is way out of my league.

501
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:38,640
Don't worry.

502
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:40,520
I know my place.

503
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:44,080
The son of a taxi driver
and a rich heiress.

504
00:37:44,160 --> 00:37:45,600
We don't belong together.

505
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:48,680
You can rest assured

506
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:50,800
that we won't be seeing each other again.

507
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:14,000
Dao.

508
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:18,160
What brings you here, Damrong?

509
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:22,040
Here.

510
00:38:22,120 --> 00:38:26,080
Petch wanted to pay back
the money you gave me.

511
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:29,080
Total silence. Are you all right?

512
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:32,240
Was I so disgusting?

513
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:33,680
Hey.

514
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,200
Don't overthink it.

515
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:38,240
Petch was just being Petch.
He meant no harm.

516
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:40,360
He just…

517
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,920
didn't want to bother you.

518
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:44,800
Do you mean that?

519
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:46,920
Yes. I mean it.

520
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:49,680
Petch and I have been
best friends for ages.

521
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,600
I can read his mind.

522
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:54,120
His words might hurt sometimes,

523
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:57,840
but I assure you that he meant no harm.

524
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:04,240
He returned the money,

525
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:07,640
but he'll come see me
at the piano competition, right?

526
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:09,600
What?

527
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:12,600
Right?

528
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:17,640
Right. He'll be there.

529
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:21,080
Dao.

530
00:39:23,640 --> 00:39:24,640
Who are you talking to?

531
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:26,080
Ake.

532
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:29,920
Who are you, punk?

533
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:32,480
Why are you here?

534
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:35,080
Ake.

535
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,120
Please watch your tone with my friend.

536
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:39,800
Dao, I thought Petch was the only lowlife

537
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:42,520
you were friends with.

538
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:43,920
Who the hell are you?

539
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:47,720
- Ake! Stop!
- Want to know me, huh?

540
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,680
Want to know me, huh?

541
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:50,680
- What, huh?
- Ake, stop!

542
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:51,840
- Can't take an insult?
- Damrong.

543
00:39:52,360 --> 00:39:53,680
Please leave, Damrong.

544
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:55,560
- Dao, move.
- Ake!

545
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:56,800
Ake!

546
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,240
What?

547
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:04,360
Coward! Where are you going?

548
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:05,480
Ake!

549
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:07,920
Please stop.

550
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:17,960
Sir.

551
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:19,800
I saw him.

552
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:21,920
That punk was hitting on Dao.

553
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:24,320
Was he?

554
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:25,360
Yes.

555
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:26,840
Dao.

556
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:28,480
Why are you behaving like this?

557
00:40:28,560 --> 00:40:30,080
- Come here!
- Honey.

558
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:33,640
We've already agreed not to hit our child.

559
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:35,360
It's against
the modern principle of parenting.

560
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:38,320
I can't stand this anymore.

561
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,520
Petch dumped her already,

562
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,560
but she's with another douche.

563
00:40:43,160 --> 00:40:48,240
Why did you lower your standards
and befriend a riffraff like that?

564
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:52,720
Mom, why do I have
to discriminate against my friends?

565
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,240
Dao.

566
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:57,000
Did you just talk back to me?

567
00:40:57,680 --> 00:41:00,360
I didn't talk back to you.
I was trying to explain.

568
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:02,080
I don't want to hear a word.

569
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,280
Dao.

570
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:05,520
You've become
a completely different person

571
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:09,320
since Petch came into your life.

572
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:10,840
Sir.

573
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:13,200
I suggest that Dao change schools.

574
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:17,560
That is a good idea.

575
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:19,880
We should send her to the US.

576
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:23,480
Send her to a high school
and a university in the US.

577
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:27,120
It is better than risking
going down the wrong path here.

578
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:28,560
Please don't.

579
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:31,160
I've never mentioned
that I want to go to the US.

580
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:34,240
The point isn't
whether you want it or not.

581
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:38,920
The point is, you do as you're told.

582
00:41:41,480 --> 00:41:42,720
In the end,

583
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,320
I'm not your daughter,

584
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:48,000
but your puppet, aren't I?

585
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:53,400
If you insist on sending me abroad,

586
00:41:54,520 --> 00:41:56,040
I won't go to school.

587
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:57,560
I won't go to the piano competition.

588
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,280
I won't do anything.

589
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,920
- Dao! Get back here!
- Ma'am.

590
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:05,520
We should leave Dao alone.

591
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:09,040
We can discuss this later
once she calms down.

592
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:11,480
Dao.

593
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:37,920
Dao.

594
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:39,280
Dao, sweetheart.

595
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:41,600
Open the door, please.

596
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:47,280
Dao.

597
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:49,840
You have a piano competition today.

598
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:54,600
Dao.

599
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:57,120
Dao!

600
00:44:58,440 --> 00:44:59,280
Hey!

601
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:01,560
Are you deaf or something?

602
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:06,960
You're testing my patience!

603
00:45:07,040 --> 00:45:07,920
Honey.

604
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:11,200
We've agreed not to raise our voices.
Let me do the talking.

605
00:45:14,520 --> 00:45:16,000
Dao, sweetie.

606
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:19,240
I think we're being too protective,

607
00:45:19,320 --> 00:45:22,560
but we'll let you
keep studying here if you want.

608
00:45:28,040 --> 00:45:29,360
Do you really mean it, Dad?

609
00:45:30,400 --> 00:45:34,960
I do. If you want to study in Thailand,
we will allow it.

610
00:45:47,960 --> 00:45:50,520
Thank you so much for understanding me.

611
00:45:50,600 --> 00:45:52,840
We've figured this out already.

612
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:56,160
Now, can you go to the competition, honey?

613
00:45:56,240 --> 00:45:59,400
Yes. I'll get ready.

614
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:10,920
Just cut her some slack.

615
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,240
We'll discuss it later,
after the competition.

616
00:46:13,320 --> 00:46:14,480
Fine, honey.

617
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:19,840
Where's Ko?

618
00:46:19,920 --> 00:46:20,960
No idea.

619
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:26,480
Here comes our big brother!

620
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:28,720
I told you.

621
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:30,720
Hell wouldn't welcome Joe that easily.

622
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:32,720
- Shut it!
- Wait!

623
00:46:33,240 --> 00:46:37,320
I mean, you're tough and hard to kill.

624
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:39,360
Right.

625
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:41,400
Congratulations.

626
00:46:41,480 --> 00:46:42,960
Physical damage can't compare

627
00:46:43,480 --> 00:46:45,320
to the mental damage.

628
00:46:46,880 --> 00:46:47,920
I will

629
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:50,040
avenge them.

630
00:46:50,640 --> 00:46:51,480
So…

631
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:53,920
Who did this to you?

632
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:56,600
And you have so many enemies.

633
00:46:57,200 --> 00:46:59,120
You're the first on my list.

634
00:46:59,920 --> 00:47:00,920
Ouch!

635
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,000
You're getting on my nerves!

636
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:03,760
Bro.

637
00:47:03,840 --> 00:47:05,440
It was just a joke, bro.

638
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:08,160
I'm with you in any fight.

639
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:11,040
Just give me the name.

640
00:47:11,880 --> 00:47:12,720
Joe!

641
00:47:13,360 --> 00:47:14,560
I got the info!

642
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:15,560
Tell me.

643
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:19,920
Bomb's gang was arrested
on the day you were ambushed.

644
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:23,080
Pao from that technician school
had a motorbike accident.

645
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:24,920
He couldn't stand on two feet
to ambush you.

646
00:47:25,960 --> 00:47:27,600
So there is only one enemy left.

647
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:32,720
It has to be him.

648
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:34,000
Who is it?

649
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:38,480
Petch.

650
00:47:42,480 --> 00:47:43,680
You're dead meat.

651
00:47:50,880 --> 00:47:51,760
Petch.

652
00:47:52,360 --> 00:47:54,240
Petch.

653
00:47:57,880 --> 00:47:58,880
What are you doing?

654
00:48:01,160 --> 00:48:02,040
Nothing.

655
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:03,400
Why?

656
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:04,920
Nothing?

657
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,640
What's behind your back?

658
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:09,640
What?

659
00:48:10,360 --> 00:48:11,480
This one.

660
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:14,360
Ta-da!

661
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:17,400
You folded paper stars
for Natedao, didn't you?

662
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,360
Obviously!

663
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:22,240
Hand it to her.

664
00:48:22,320 --> 00:48:23,160
Hey.

665
00:48:23,880 --> 00:48:25,080
What's wrong with you?

666
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:28,360
Dao will be
at the piano competition tonight.

667
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:32,040
I want you to give this to her.

668
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:35,280
You made this, so give it to her yourself.

669
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:39,040
I've returned the invitation card.

670
00:48:42,800 --> 00:48:43,680
Wait a second.

671
00:48:44,960 --> 00:48:46,280
The invitation card…

672
00:48:52,720 --> 00:48:55,320
I still have it with me. Here.
Give it to her yourself.

673
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:02,280
Here.

674
00:49:02,360 --> 00:49:03,840
Give it to her yourself.

675
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:30,200
Hello? What's up, Dam?

676
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:32,320
You forgot the paper stars here.

677
00:49:33,600 --> 00:49:35,360
Thanks. I'm heading back to fetch it.

678
00:49:37,280 --> 00:49:39,080
Hello, buddy.

679
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:40,680
Do you recognize me?

680
00:49:40,760 --> 00:49:42,800
I never had buddies like you.

681
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:44,560
You're only the protagonist's buddy then?

682
00:49:45,160 --> 00:49:46,320
You know what?

683
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:49,000
The protagonist's buddy
always dies in the end.

684
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:57,600
Dam!

685
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:06,320
NEXT EPISODE

686
00:50:14,360 --> 00:50:15,320
Dao, watch out!

687
00:50:18,600 --> 00:50:19,800
Go.

688
00:50:20,520 --> 00:50:21,400
- Dad.
- Petch!

689
00:50:21,480 --> 00:50:22,840
Dad!

690
00:50:22,920 --> 00:50:23,880
<i>Let go of my son!</i>

691
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:25,840
<i>Let go of my son!</i>

692
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:42,400
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

693
00:50:43,560 --> 00:50:48,640
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

694
00:50:49,440 --> 00:50:55,400
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

695
00:50:55,480 --> 00:51:00,040
<i>But never reaching you</i>

696
00:51:01,160 --> 00:51:06,200
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

697
00:51:07,240 --> 00:51:12,040
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

698
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:19,200
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

699
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:23,520
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

700
00:51:23,600 --> 00:51:25,120
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
